# CIFAR-10 Image Classification using CNN

## 📌 Overview

Built a Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) to classify color images into 10 object categories using the CIFAR-10 dataset.

✔ Multi-class image classification (10 classes)
✔ Achieved ~75–80% test accuracy
✔ Applied regularization techniques to reduce overfitting

---

## 📂 Dataset

* Dataset: CIFAR-10
* Source: keras.datasets.cifar10 (built-in)
* Total Classes: 10
* Image Size: 32×32 (RGB)

### Classes:

```
airplane, automobile, bird, cat, deer,
dog, frog, horse, ship, truck
```

---

## ⚙️ Approach

### 1. Data Preprocessing

* Normalized pixel values (0–1)
* No resizing required (already 32×32)
* Labels kept in integer format

---

### 2. Model Architecture

```
Conv2D (32 filters) + ReLU  
Batch Normalization  
Conv2D (32 filters) + ReLU  
MaxPooling  
Dropout (0.25)  

Conv2D (64 filters) + ReLU  
Batch Normalization  
Conv2D (64 filters) + ReLU  
MaxPooling  
Dropout (0.25)  

Conv2D (128 filters) + ReLU  
Batch Normalization  
MaxPooling  
Dropout (0.3)  

Flatten  
Dense (256) + ReLU  
Dropout (0.5)  

Output Layer (10 classes, Softmax)
```

---

### 3. Training

* Optimizer: Adam
* Loss: Sparse Categorical Crossentropy
* Epochs: 15–20
* Batch Size: 128

---

## 📊 Results

* Training Accuracy: ~85–90%
* Test Accuracy: ~75–80%

### 📈 Observations

* Model performs well on distinct objects (airplane, ship)
* Confusion observed between similar classes:

  * cat vs dog
  * automobile vs truck

---

## 🧠 Key Insights

* Small image size (32×32) limits feature extraction
* Deeper networks improve performance but increase overfitting risk
* Regularization (Dropout + BatchNorm) significantly improves generalization

---

